{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is the venue"},{"time":3000,"text":"where, as a young man,"},{"time":5000,"text":"some of the music that I wrote was first performed."},{"time":8000,"text":"It was, remarkably,"},{"time":10000,"text":"a pretty good sounding room."},{"time":12000,"text":"With all the uneven walls and all the crap everywhere,"},{"time":14000,"text":"it actually sounded pretty good."},{"time":16000,"text":"This is a song that was recorded there."},{"time":19000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":21000,"text":"This is not Talking Heads,"},{"time":24000,"text":"in the picture anyway."},{"time":26000,"text":"(Music: \"A Clean Break (Let's Work)\" by Talking Heads)"},{"time":34000,"text":"So the nature of the room"},{"time":36000,"text":"meant that words could be understood."},{"time":38000,"text":"The lyrics of the songs could be pretty much understood."},{"time":40000,"text":"The sound system was kind of decent."},{"time":43000,"text":"And there wasn't a lot of reverberation in the room."},{"time":46000,"text":"So the rhythms"},{"time":48000,"text":"could be pretty intact too,"},{"time":50000,"text":"pretty concise."},{"time":52000,"text":"Other places around the country had similar rooms."},{"time":54000,"text":"This is Tootsie's Orchid Lounge in Nashville."},{"time":57000,"text":"The music was in some ways different,"},{"time":59000,"text":"but in structure and form,"},{"time":62000,"text":"very much the same."},{"time":64000,"text":"The clientele behavior was very much the same too."},{"time":69000,"text":"And so the bands at Tootsie's"},{"time":71000,"text":"or at CBGB's"},{"time":73000,"text":"had to play loud enough --"},{"time":76000,"text":"the volume had to be loud enough to overcome"},{"time":78000,"text":"people falling down, shouting out"},{"time":80000,"text":"and doing whatever else they were doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"Since then, I've played other places"},{"time":84000,"text":"that are much nicer."},{"time":86000,"text":"I've played the Disney Hall here"},{"time":89000,"text":"and Carnegie Hall and places like that."},{"time":92000,"text":"And it's been very exciting."},{"time":94000,"text":"But I also noticed that sometimes the music"},{"time":96000,"text":"that I had written,"},{"time":98000,"text":"or was writing at the time,"},{"time":100000,"text":"didn't sound all that great"},{"time":102000,"text":"in some of those halls."},{"time":104000,"text":"We managed,"},{"time":106000,"text":"but sometimes those halls didn't seem exactly suited"},{"time":109000,"text":"to the music I was making"},{"time":111000,"text":"or had made."},{"time":113000,"text":"So I asked myself:"},{"time":115000,"text":"Do I write stuff"},{"time":116000,"text":"for specific rooms?"},{"time":118000,"text":"Do I have a place, a venue,"},{"time":120000,"text":"in mind when I write?"},{"time":122000,"text":"Is that a kind of model for creativity?"},{"time":124000,"text":"Do we all make things with"},{"time":126000,"text":"a venue, a context, in mind?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"Okay, Africa."},{"time":132000,"text":"(Music: \"Wenlenga\" / Various artists)"},{"time":139000,"text":"Most of the popular music that we know now"},{"time":142000,"text":"has a big part of its roots in West Africa."},{"time":145000,"text":"And the music there,"},{"time":147000,"text":"I would say, the instruments,"},{"time":149000,"text":"the intricate rhythms,"},{"time":151000,"text":"the way it's played, the setting, the context,"},{"time":154000,"text":"it's all perfect. It all works perfect."},{"time":156000,"text":"The music works perfectly in that setting."},{"time":159000,"text":"There's no big room"},{"time":161000,"text":"to create reverberation and confuse the rhythms."},{"time":164000,"text":"The instruments are loud enough"},{"time":166000,"text":"that they can be heard without amplification, etc., etc."},{"time":168000,"text":"It's no accident."},{"time":170000,"text":"It's perfect for that particular context."},{"time":173000,"text":"And it would be a mess"},{"time":175000,"text":"in a context like this. This is a gothic cathedral."},{"time":178000,"text":"(Music: \"Spem In Alium\" by Thomas Tallis)"},{"time":184000,"text":"In a gothic cathedral, this kind of music is perfect."},{"time":190000,"text":"It doesn't change key, the notes are long,"},{"time":192000,"text":"there's almost no rhythm whatsoever,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and the room flatters the music."},{"time":199000,"text":"It actually improves it."},{"time":201000,"text":"This is the room that Bach"},{"time":203000,"text":"wrote some of his music for. This is the organ."},{"time":206000,"text":"It's not as big as a gothic cathedral,"},{"time":208000,"text":"so he can write things that are a little bit more intricate."},{"time":211000,"text":"He can, very innovatively,"},{"time":213000,"text":"actually change keys"},{"time":215000,"text":"without risking huge dissonances."},{"time":217000,"text":"(Music: \"Fantasia On Jesu, Mein Freunde\" by Johann S. Bach)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"This is a little bit later."},{"time":227000,"text":"This is the kind of rooms that Mozart wrote in."},{"time":230000,"text":"I think we're in like 1770, somewhere around there."},{"time":233000,"text":"They're smaller, even less reverberant,"},{"time":235000,"text":"so he can write really frilly music"},{"time":237000,"text":"that's very intricate -- and it works."},{"time":241000,"text":"(Music: \"Sonata in F,\" KV 13, by Wolfgang A. Mozart)"},{"time":244000,"text":"It fits the room perfectly."},{"time":250000,"text":"This is La Scala."},{"time":252000,"text":"It's around the same time,"},{"time":254000,"text":"I think it was built around 1776."},{"time":256000,"text":"People in the audience in these opera houses, when they were built,"},{"time":259000,"text":"they used to yell out to one another."},{"time":261000,"text":"They used to eat, drink and yell out to people on the stage,"},{"time":264000,"text":"just like they do at CBGB's and places like that."},{"time":266000,"text":"If they liked an aria,"},{"time":268000,"text":"they would holler and suggest"},{"time":270000,"text":"that it be done again as an encore,"},{"time":272000,"text":"not at the end of the show, but immediately."},{"time":275000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":279000,"text":"And well, that was an opera experience."},{"time":282000,"text":"This is the opera house that Wagner built for himself."},{"time":286000,"text":"And the size of the room is not that big."},{"time":289000,"text":"It's smaller than this."},{"time":291000,"text":"But Wagner made an innovation."},{"time":293000,"text":"He wanted a bigger band."},{"time":295000,"text":"He wanted a little more bombast,"},{"time":297000,"text":"so he increased the size of the orchestra pit"},{"time":299000,"text":"so he could get more low-end instruments in there."},{"time":302000,"text":"(Music: \"Lohengrin / Prelude to Act III\" by Richard Wagner)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"Okay."},{"time":315000,"text":"This is Carnegie Hall."},{"time":318000,"text":"Obviously, this kind of thing became popular."},{"time":320000,"text":"The halls got bigger. Carnegie Hall's fair-sized."},{"time":323000,"text":"It's larger than some of the other symphony halls."},{"time":326000,"text":"And they're a lot more reverberant"},{"time":328000,"text":"than La Scala."},{"time":330000,"text":"Around the same,"},{"time":332000,"text":"according to Alex Ross who writes for the New Yorker,"},{"time":335000,"text":"this kind of rule came into effect"},{"time":338000,"text":"that audiences had to be quiet --"},{"time":340000,"text":"no more eating, drinking and yelling at the stage,"},{"time":342000,"text":"or gossiping with one another"},{"time":344000,"text":"during the show."},{"time":346000,"text":"They had to be very quiet."},{"time":348000,"text":"So those two things combined meant that"},{"time":350000,"text":"a different kind of music"},{"time":352000,"text":"worked best in these kind of halls."},{"time":355000,"text":"It meant that there could be extreme dynamics,"},{"time":357000,"text":"which there weren't in some of these"},{"time":359000,"text":"other kinds of music."},{"time":361000,"text":"Quiet parts could be heard"},{"time":363000,"text":"that would have been drowned out"},{"time":365000,"text":"by all the gossiping and shouting."},{"time":367000,"text":"But because of the reverberation"},{"time":369000,"text":"in those rooms like Carnegie Hall,"},{"time":371000,"text":"the music had to be maybe a little less rhythmic"},{"time":373000,"text":"and a little more textural."},{"time":375000,"text":"(Music: \"Symphony No. 8 in E Flat Major\" by Gustav Mahler)"},{"time":378000,"text":"This is Mahler."},{"time":381000,"text":"It looks like Bob Dylan, but it's Mahler."},{"time":386000,"text":"That was Bob's last record, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":392000,"text":"Popular music, coming along at the same time."},{"time":395000,"text":"This is a jazz band."},{"time":397000,"text":"According to Scott Joplin, the bands were playing"},{"time":400000,"text":"on riverboats and clubs."},{"time":402000,"text":"Again, it's noisy. They're playing for dancers."},{"time":404000,"text":"There's certain sections of the song -- the songs had different sections"},{"time":407000,"text":"that the dancers really liked."},{"time":409000,"text":"And they'd say, \"Play that part again.\""},{"time":411000,"text":"Well, there's only so many times"},{"time":413000,"text":"you can play the same section of a song over and over again for the dancers."},{"time":416000,"text":"So the bands started to improvise new melodies."},{"time":419000,"text":"And a new form of music was born."},{"time":421000,"text":"(Music: \"Royal Garden Blues\" by W.C. Handy / Ethel Waters)"},{"time":431000,"text":"These are played mainly in small rooms."},{"time":435000,"text":"People are dancing, shouting and drinking."},{"time":437000,"text":"So the music has to be loud enough"},{"time":439000,"text":"to be heard above that."},{"time":441000,"text":"Same thing goes true for -- that's the beginning of the century --"},{"time":444000,"text":"for the whole of 20th-century popular music,"},{"time":447000,"text":"whether it's rock or Latin music or whatever."},{"time":449000,"text":"[Live music] doesn't really change that much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452000,"text":"It changes about a third of the way into the 20th century,"},{"time":455000,"text":"when this became"},{"time":458000,"text":"one of the primary venues for music."},{"time":461000,"text":"And this was one way"},{"time":463000,"text":"that the music got there."},{"time":465000,"text":"Microphones enabled singers, in particular,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and musicians and composers,"},{"time":470000,"text":"to completely change the kind of music"},{"time":472000,"text":"that they were writing."},{"time":474000,"text":"So far, a lot of the stuff that was on the radio was live music,"},{"time":477000,"text":"but singers, like Frank Sinatra,"},{"time":480000,"text":"could use the mic"},{"time":482000,"text":"and do things"},{"time":484000,"text":"that they could never do without a microphone."},{"time":487000,"text":"Other singers after him"},{"time":489000,"text":"went even further."},{"time":491000,"text":"(Music: \"My Funny Valentine\" by Chet Baker)"},{"time":498000,"text":"This is Chet Baker."},{"time":500000,"text":"And this kind of thing"},{"time":502000,"text":"would have been impossible without a microphone."},{"time":504000,"text":"It would have been impossible without recorded music as well."},{"time":507000,"text":"And he's singing right into your ear."},{"time":509000,"text":"He's whispering into your ears."},{"time":511000,"text":"The effect is just electric."},{"time":513000,"text":"It's like the guy is sitting next to you,"},{"time":515000,"text":"whispering who knows what into your ear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"So at this point, music diverged."},{"time":522000,"text":"There's live music,"},{"time":524000,"text":"and there's recorded music."},{"time":526000,"text":"And they no longer have to be exactly the same."},{"time":529000,"text":"Now there's venues like this, a discotheque,"},{"time":532000,"text":"and there's jukeboxes in bars,"},{"time":534000,"text":"where you don't even need to have a band."},{"time":536000,"text":"There doesn't need to be any"},{"time":538000,"text":"live performing musicians whatsoever,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and the sound systems are good."},{"time":544000,"text":"People began to make music"},{"time":546000,"text":"specifically for discos"},{"time":549000,"text":"and for those sound systems."},{"time":551000,"text":"And, as with jazz,"},{"time":554000,"text":"the dancers liked certain sections"},{"time":557000,"text":"more than they did others."},{"time":559000,"text":"So the early hip-hop guys would loop certain sections."},{"time":562000,"text":"(Music: \"Rapper's Delight\" by The Sugarhill Gang)"},{"time":570000,"text":"The MC would improvise lyrics"},{"time":572000,"text":"in the same way that the jazz players would improvise melodies."},{"time":575000,"text":"And another new form of music was born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"Live performance, when it was incredibly successful,"},{"time":582000,"text":"ended up in what is probably, acoustically,"},{"time":585000,"text":"the worst sounding venues on the planet:"},{"time":588000,"text":"sports stadiums,"},{"time":590000,"text":"basketball arenas and hockey arenas."},{"time":593000,"text":"Musicians who ended up there did the best they could."},{"time":595000,"text":"They wrote what is now called arena rock,"},{"time":597000,"text":"which is medium-speed ballads."},{"time":599000,"text":"(Music: \"I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For\" by U2)"},{"time":607000,"text":"They did the best they could"},{"time":609000,"text":"given that this is what they're writing for."},{"time":612000,"text":"The tempos are medium. It sounds big."},{"time":615000,"text":"It's more a social situation"},{"time":617000,"text":"than a musical situation."},{"time":619000,"text":"And in some ways, the music"},{"time":621000,"text":"that they're writing for this place"},{"time":623000,"text":"works perfectly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626000,"text":"So there's more new venues."},{"time":629000,"text":"One of the new ones is the automobile."},{"time":631000,"text":"I grew up with a radio in a car."},{"time":633000,"text":"But now that's evolved into something else."},{"time":635000,"text":"The car is a whole venue."},{"time":637000,"text":"(Music: \"Who U Wit\" by Lil' Jon &amp; the East Side Boyz)"},{"time":642000,"text":"The music that, I would say, is written"},{"time":645000,"text":"for automobile sound systems"},{"time":647000,"text":"works perfectly on it."},{"time":649000,"text":"It might not be what you want to listen to at home,"},{"time":652000,"text":"but it works great in the car --"},{"time":654000,"text":"has a huge frequency spectrum,"},{"time":657000,"text":"you know, big bass and high-end"},{"time":659000,"text":"and the voice kind of stuck in the middle."},{"time":662000,"text":"Automobile music, you can share with your friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"There's one other kind of new venue,"},{"time":668000,"text":"the private MP3 player."},{"time":671000,"text":"Presumably, this is just for Christian music."},{"time":673000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":679000,"text":"And in some ways it's like Carnegie Hall,"},{"time":682000,"text":"or when the audience had to hush up,"},{"time":684000,"text":"because you can now hear every single detail."},{"time":687000,"text":"In other ways, it's more like the West African music"},{"time":689000,"text":"because if the music in an MP3 player gets too quiet,"},{"time":692000,"text":"you turn it up, and the next minute,"},{"time":694000,"text":"your ears are blasted out by a louder passage."},{"time":697000,"text":"So that doesn't really work."},{"time":699000,"text":"I think pop music, mainly,"},{"time":701000,"text":"it's written today,"},{"time":703000,"text":"to some extent, is written for these kind of players,"},{"time":706000,"text":"for this kind of personal experience"},{"time":708000,"text":"where you can hear extreme detail,"},{"time":710000,"text":"but the dynamic doesn't change that much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"So I asked myself:"},{"time":716000,"text":"Okay, is this"},{"time":718000,"text":"a model for creation,"},{"time":720000,"text":"this adaptation that we do?"},{"time":723000,"text":"And does it happen anywhere else?"},{"time":725000,"text":"Well, according to David Attenborough and some other people,"},{"time":728000,"text":"birds do it too --"},{"time":730000,"text":"that the birds in the canopy,"},{"time":733000,"text":"where the foliage is dense,"},{"time":735000,"text":"their calls tend to be"},{"time":737000,"text":"high-pitched, short and repetitive."},{"time":741000,"text":"And the birds on the floor"},{"time":743000,"text":"tend to have lower pitched calls,"},{"time":745000,"text":"so that they don't get distorted"},{"time":747000,"text":"when they bounce off the forest floor."},{"time":750000,"text":"And birds like this Savannah sparrow,"},{"time":754000,"text":"they tend to have a buzzing"},{"time":756000,"text":"(Sound clip: Savannah sparrow song)"},{"time":758000,"text":"type call."},{"time":760000,"text":"And it turns out that"},{"time":763000,"text":"a sound like this"},{"time":765000,"text":"is the most energy efficient and practical way"},{"time":768000,"text":"to transmit their call"},{"time":771000,"text":"across the fields and savannahs."},{"time":775000,"text":"Other birds, like this tanager,"},{"time":778000,"text":"have adapted within the same species."},{"time":781000,"text":"The tananger on the East Coast of the United States,"},{"time":783000,"text":"where the forests are a little denser,"},{"time":785000,"text":"has one kind of call,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and the tananger on the other side, on the west"},{"time":790000,"text":"(Sound clip: Scarlet tanager song)"},{"time":792000,"text":"has a different kind of call."},{"time":795000,"text":"(Sound clip: Scarlet tanager song)"},{"time":800000,"text":"So birds do it too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"And I thought:"},{"time":805000,"text":"Well, if this is a model for creation,"},{"time":808000,"text":"if we make music,"},{"time":810000,"text":"primarily the form at least,"},{"time":813000,"text":"to fit these contexts,"},{"time":815000,"text":"and if we make art to fit gallery walls or museum walls,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and if we write software to fit existing operating systems,"},{"time":823000,"text":"is that how it works?"},{"time":826000,"text":"Yeah. I think it's evolutionary."},{"time":828000,"text":"It's adaptive."},{"time":830000,"text":"But the pleasure and the passion and the joy"},{"time":832000,"text":"is still there."},{"time":835000,"text":"This is a reverse view of things"},{"time":837000,"text":"from the kind of traditional Romantic view."},{"time":839000,"text":"The Romantic view is that"},{"time":841000,"text":"first comes the passion"},{"time":843000,"text":"and then the outpouring of emotion,"},{"time":845000,"text":"and then somehow it gets shaped into something."},{"time":848000,"text":"And I'm saying,"},{"time":850000,"text":"well, the passion's still there,"},{"time":852000,"text":"but the vessel"},{"time":854000,"text":"that it's going to be injected into and poured into,"},{"time":857000,"text":"that is instinctively and intuitively"},{"time":859000,"text":"created first."},{"time":861000,"text":"We already know where that passion is going."},{"time":868000,"text":"But this conflict of views is kind of interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"The writer,"},{"time":873000,"text":"Thomas Frank,"},{"time":875000,"text":"says that"},{"time":877000,"text":"this might be a kind of explanation"},{"time":879000,"text":"why some voters vote"},{"time":881000,"text":"against their best interests,"},{"time":883000,"text":"that voters, like a lot of us,"},{"time":886000,"text":"assume, that if they hear something that sounds like it's sincere,"},{"time":889000,"text":"that it's coming from the gut, that it's passionate,"},{"time":891000,"text":"that it's more authentic."},{"time":893000,"text":"And they'll vote for that."},{"time":895000,"text":"So that, if somebody can fake sincerity,"},{"time":897000,"text":"if they can fake passion,"},{"time":900000,"text":"they stand a better chance"},{"time":902000,"text":"of being selected in that way,"},{"time":906000,"text":"which seems a little dangerous."},{"time":910000,"text":"I'm saying the two, the passion, the joy,"},{"time":913000,"text":"are not mutually exclusive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"Maybe what the world needs now is for us to realize"},{"time":918000,"text":"that we are like the birds."},{"time":920000,"text":"We adapt."},{"time":922000,"text":"We sing."},{"time":924000,"text":"And like the birds, the joy is still there,"},{"time":926000,"text":"even though we have changed what we do"},{"time":929000,"text":"to fit the context."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}